apiKey
data.description: The API Key for this project. If the key you provide is invalid, we’ll return a 400 Bad Request error.

data.name: eventName
data.description: The name of the event. Must be between 1 and 255 characters in length, and cannot be null.

data.name: eventTime
data.description: The time that the event occurred, in milliseconds. This field is optional, and will default to the current time if not set. Events with negative timestamps (i.e., dates before 1970 UTC) will be rejected.

data.name: eventUniqueId
data.description: The unique identifier for the user triggering the event. Must be between 1 and 255 characters in length, and cannot be null.

data.name: properties
data.description: An internal JSON Object, listing property names and values as Strings. Values have a maximum length of 255 characters.
